 for bestpractices and # User Profile Page

## Overview
Develop a fully functional User Profile Page for LifeOps Personal that enables users to view and edit public/private profile settings, personal preferences, and a short bio. Integrate optional Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) via authenticator apps and backup codes, and provide CRUD management for user profile data, preferences, visibility controls, timezone, and currency settings. The page should be mobile-first, accessible, and visually aligned with the LifeOps Personal design system (warm yellow accents, clean cards, soft elevation, and responsive 2–3 column layouts on larger screens). All data interactions must be resilient to null/undefined values and guarded against common runtime errors as per the runtime safety rules.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A centralized User Profile Page that allows users to manage their personal presence, privacy visibility, and preferences, including a short bio. It also serves as the control center for enabling/disabling 2FA and managing recovery codes, along with CRUD operations for profile data (name, avatar, bio, social links), visibility settings (which fields are public or private), timezone, currency, and units.

Goals:
- Provide a user-friendly interface to view and update profile data, manage who can see what, configure personal preferences, and secure the account through optional 2FA.
- Ensure data integrity by validating inputs, guarding against null/undefined data, and providing clear success/error feedback.
- Seamlessly connect to authentication/authorization layers, profile services, and any required backend APIs (or mock APIs in development) to persist changes.
- Maintain UI consistency with the LifeOps Personal design system: card-based sections, interactive controls, bottom navigation on mobile, and a prominent FAB for quick actions where appropriate.

Connected features:
- Two-Factor Authentication: Optional 2FA via authenticator apps and backup codes for sensitive actions (e.g., changing security settings, exporting data).
- User Profile Management: CRUD operations for profile fields (name, avatar, bio, social handles), preferences (timezone, currency, units), and visibility controls (public/private data sharing).
- Activity Summary: Quick stats such as number of published items, projects, or activity score (optional micro-analytics to surface user engagement).

UI elements and guidance:
- Profile Card: Avatar, display name, handle, and quick social links.
- Bio Editor: Short bio with character limit indicator and live validation.
- Visibility Controls: Toggles or segmented controls to determine which fields are public (name, bio, social links, avatar, activity status).
- Personal Preferences: Timezone selector, currency selector, and units (metric/imperial).
- 2FA Section: Setup/disable flow, QR code display for authenticator apps, provisioning code backup codes, and recovery code display with copy actions.
- Activity Summary: Lightweight metrics with clean visuals and accessible labels.
- Navigation: Fixed bottom navigation on mobile, with a central FAB for key actions (e.g., “Save All” or “Add Profile Photo”) and optional drawers on larger devices.

API integrations:
- This prompt assumes no hard-coded API endpoints. Design endpoints and data flows to work with: authentication service (for 2FA actions), user/profile service (CRUD for profile, preferences, visibility, timezone, currency), and 2FA management (generate/verify codes, backup codes). Include clear error handling for network issues and authorization failures.

CRITICAL: Ensure all runtime safety rules are followed (see “Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety” section). No APIless assumptions that could yield undefined values.

## Components to Build
- UserProfilePage (container)
  - Subsections:
    - ProfileOverviewCard: avatar, name, handle, social links, and quick actions.
    - BioEditorCard: short bio with character limit, live validation, and save.
    - VisibilityCard: toggles for public fields (name, bio, avatar, social links, activity).
    - PreferencesCard: timezone, currency, units, and related settings.
    - TwoFactorCard: 2FA setup/disable, authenticator app provisioning, backup codes, recovery codes management.
    - ActivitySummaryCard (optional): small charts or stat tiles (uses restrained color palette).
  - ActionBar / Floating Action Button (FAB): central yellow FAB for primary action (e.g., Save All or Quick Edit).
- AvatarUploader
  - Drag-and-drop or click-to-select image, preview, client-side validation (size/type), and removal.
- TimezoneSelector
  - Searchable dropdown or list with common timezones; supports partial matches.
- CurrencySelector
  - Dropdown with currency codes and symbols; supports locale-aware display.
- VisibilityToggle
  - Reusable toggle component with aria-labels and keyboard accessible interactions.
- TwoFactorSetupWizard
  - Stepper-like UI for enabling 2FA: scanning QR code, entering TOTP, generating/storing backup codes.
- NotificationToast
  - Reusable to display success or error messages with accessible ARIA roles.
- DataGridRow/InfoRow
  - For consistent rendering of profile data rows or preference items.
- ValidationMessage
  - Inline validation indicators and helper text.

Technical details per component:
- All lists/collections must guard against null/undefined: use (array ?? []) and Array.isArray checks where appropriate.
- All forms must initialize state with typed defaults: useState<string>("") or useState<string[]>([])/useState<T[]>([]).
- Use consistent error boundaries and loading indicators for API interactions.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI Components:
  - Build responsive Card-based layout with Inter font, matching color palette, typography, and spacing guidelines.
  - Ensure accessibility: semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, and sufficient color contrast (WCAG AA).
  - Form controls: labeled inputs with clear focus states, 12–14px radii, border colors, and focus rings (#FDE047 or #FFD400).
  - Input validation: enforce character limits (bio), required fields (name), valid URLs for social links, and proper timezone/currency selections.
  - 2FA flow: QR code rendering (image generated by backend or authenticator from shared secret), input for verification code, and backup codes export with copy functionality.
  - Avatar uploader: file input with client-side image preview, size validation, and drag-and-drop.
  - Data safety: guard all array/mapping operations with (array ?? []) or Array.isArray(array) checks.
- State management:
  - Use React hooks with proper typing: useState<T[]>([]) for arrays, useState<T | null> for optional values, and useEffect for side effects.
  - Debounce bio updates or auto-save with explicit save action to avoid partial writes.
- API communication:
  - Provide well-typed fetch/axios calls with response validation:
    - const profile = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
    - Use data ?? [] for lists from the backend
  - Implement error handling for 4xx/5xx with user-friendly messages.
  - Ensure API responses are validated: const profileData = response?.data ?? {} ; const items = Array.isArray(profileData?.items) ? profileData.items : []
- Data validation and guards:
  - All array operations guarded: (items ?? []).map(...)
  - Optional chaining for nested API responses: api?.data?.user?.profile
  - Destructuring with defaults: const { bio = "", name = "", timezone = "", currency = "" } = profile ?? {}
- Styling:
  - Implement design system tokens for colors, radii, shadows, and typography.
  - Use the provided color palette, gradient, and typography guidelines.
  - Implement responsive grid: single column on mobile; 2–3 columns on larger viewports.
- Performance:
  - Lazy load profile data, avoid unnecessary re-renders, and memoize pure subcomponents where possible.

### Backend
- APIs (design the endpoints, methods, and payloads):
  - GET /api/profile -> fetch profile data (public fields, private fields if authorized)
  - PUT /api/profile -> update profile data (name, bio, avatarUrl, socialLinks, visibility)
  - PATCH /api/profile/preferences -> update timezone, currency, units
  - POST /api/profile/avatar -> upload avatar image (multipart/form-data)
  - GET /api/profile/visibility -> fetch visibility settings
  - PUT /api/profile/visibility -> update visibility settings
  - POST /api/profile/2fa/setup -> initiate 2FA (generate secret, return QR code URL)
  - POST /api/profile/2fa/verify -> verify TOTP code and enable 2FA
  - GET /api/profile/2fa/backup-codes -> fetch generated backup codes (masked)
  - POST /api/profile/2fa/backup-codes -> generate new backup codes
  - POST /api/profile/2fa/disable -> disable 2FA
- Database schema (example; adapt to your ORM):
  - users
    - id (UUID), name, handle, bio, avatarUrl, publicProfile (boolean)
  - user_preferences
    - user_id (FK), timezone, currency, units (metric/imperial), visibility_settings (JSON)
  - user_2fa
    - user_id (FK), is_enabled (boolean), secret (encrypted), recovery_codes (JSON), emergency_contact (optional)
- Validation and security:
  - Validate all inputs on server-side as well (lengths, formats, allowed values).
  - Enforce authentication for sensitive operations (PUT/POST/PATCH to profile, 2FA).
  - Encrypt sensitive data (2FA secret) at rest; never reveal secrets in API responses beyond what’s necessary for verification.
  - Rate limit 2FA attempts and backup code generation to prevent abuse.
  - Ensure null-safe responses: always return consistent shapes; nulls mapped to defaults on the client.

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - UserProfilePage fetches profile and visibility on mount; populates components.
  - Edits are staged in local state and saved via PUT/PATCH endpoints; optimistic UI updates with rollback on error.
  - 2FA setup provides provisioning secret, QR code rendering client-side via an image URL from backend; verify code to enable 2FA; backup codes retrieval/generation flows.
  - Avatar upload triggers avatar endpoint; on success, update avatarUrl in profile.
- Error handling:
  - Centralized error toastor with contextual messages.
  - Show skeletons/loading indicators while data loads.
- Validation:
  - Client-side validation with per-field messages; server-side validation on submission.

## User Experience Flow
1. User opens the User Profile Page on mobile or desktop.
2. On load, profile data (name, bio, avatar, social links) and preferences (timezone, currency, units) are fetched; visibility settings and 2FA status are retrieved.
3. User edits profile fields:
   - Change name, bio (character limit observed), avatar (upload), social links.
   - Toggle visibility for each field (public/private).
   - Update timezone, currency, units.
4. User scrolls to 2FA section:
   - If 2FA is disabled, option to enable: backend returns a secret and a QR code; user scans with authenticator app, enters TOTP code to verify; upon success, 2FA is enabled and backup codes are generated or available.
   - If 2FA is enabled, user can disable after re-verifying a TOTP code and/or re-authenticating.
   - Backup codes can be regenerated or exported (copy to clipboard).
5. User taps the primary FAB (e.g., “Save All”) to persist all staged changes; show inline validation and a success toast on completion.
6. All changes reflect immediately in UI with a non-blocking optimistic update; any errors revert and show helpful messages.
7. All interactions should work with the designed bottom navigation on mobile and a clean multi-column layout on larger screens.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:
  - UserProfile
    - id: string
    - name: string
    - handle: string
    - bio: string
    - avatarUrl: string | null
    - socialLinks: { platform: string, url: string }[]  // guard with (array ?? [])
    - publicProfile: boolean
  - UserPreferences
    - userId: string
    - timezone: string
    - currency: string
    - units: 'metric' | 'imperial'
  - VisibilitySettings
    - userId: string
    - fields: {
        name: boolean
        avatar: boolean
        bio: boolean
        socialLinks: boolean
        activity: boolean
      }
  - User2FA
    - userId: string
    - isEnabled: boolean
    - secret: string | null
    - backupCodes: string[]
- API Endpoints (RESTful design as above)
- Security:
  - JWT or session-based authentication for user-specific endpoints.
  - OAuth-safe practices for auth flows if needed.
